elements

### Description

This component works as expected inside Angular app - after manually appending `/?foo=bar` to URL I can see `bar` printed in the console.

```ts
export class ActivatedRouteComponent implements OnInit {
  route = inject(ActivatedRoute);

  ngOnInit() {
    this.route.queryParamMap.subscribe((paramMap) =>
      console.log(paramMap.get('foo')),
    );
  }
}
```

But after exporting it as web component using angular-elements it doesn't work - `null` printed once.

